caption: Worst service I’ve ever received at a restaurant. Took over an hour to get my food, and we ordered right when we sat down. Will never come again. There’s a reason it’s not popular among Georgetown students.
Came in stressed, confused and lost! Met Janai and my mood was lifted immediately! She was kind kind, sweet and made me smile.
Good people, and good menus

YIKES. I used to come here a lot for takeout, and it was always good. The good news is, food is still solid. However, the service is literally worthy of zero stars - the hostess was texting when we walked in and just pointed us to a table instead of walking us there. Menus were dirty. Refills were brought around once. Dessert took over 20 minutes to come out. Couldn't recommend it, sorry.
I liked the Mediterranean salad without chicken and loved the mint-cucumber sauce they served with it. It is convenient for Hoyas and one of the good hangout places on sunny days.
Phenomenal service and lovely place to have a drink after class.
The food its ok, yet Christian makes it a better place.

A good place to get a good meal while on the Georgetown campus.

Fun outdoor/indoor spot on campus, has a good mix of bar food and easy going drinks. Really shines when you have groups and can hang out on the top level terrace. Provides some nice views over the river and space to relax and talk. Nothing over the top, but perfect for what it is.
Good happy hour specials.
Service was pretty slow, but the food was tasty!
Nice on campus Pub. Little expensive for college kids.

Karaoke was awesome!
Still slow service, but good food.

Bulldog had been very disappointing under previous owners (especially last year) but things seem to have really turned around now! The sweet potato fries and grilled cheese were great and good value (for DC, at least), and service at the to-go window is quick!
Quality of food is getting worse.

The Bulldog Tavern re-opened and the service there has improved since the management and staff changed. The food served now is made fairly quickly no, with the longest wait time being 10 minutes or so, however considering the wait time before that was 30 minutes to an hour, this is a welcome change. The tavern also now serves alcohol and other simple mixed drinks! A place worth checking out seeing how there are places to study right outside and who doesn't like a foods break from studying!?!?!
Expensive, overpriced and low quality of service. Sold to college students who shouldn't be drinking expensive beer if they are taking out $100k in student loans.
good Hoya Burger. Price was lower than most places in the area. Nice deck. order at the to go window.
No it's under remodelation. Student place.
Slow but I love the food and beer
Confort food, drinks, and baseball. Need I say more?
Don't go . place is 👎

Bulldog Tavern is the absolute worst. Terrible ordering system, terrible wait times for mediocre food. I would literally rather eat anything else if I could but it’s the only option open at this time on campus. F bulldog and F Georgetown dining services
Avoid

Terrible service even with almost no one in the place.  Waiter disappeared and orders took over an hour for burgers and wings.   When I asked about the wait he said the kitchen was really backed up from online orders.  Orders came out as partial and at different times.  We’ve been here before.  Never been anywhere near this bad.

We came to Georgetown to visit our son and decided to eat something at the restaurant. As soon as the server Kevin came we ordered 2 drinks and 2 burgers. After several minutes we noticed that he was on the entrance checking his cellphone and didn’t order our drinks. We had to call another waitress, she called him and after that, he rushed to the bar to get our drinks. When I asked for our check, he told me that the machine was broken and that I had cash to pay. I didn’t have much cash at the moment and I decided to pay with credit card, he definitely wasn’t happy about it and told me “you have to tip me in cash”.  We left the restaurant feeling very uncomfortable for such as bad experience with the timing for our orders and the weird request from your server. This is a shame for this restaurant inside of such a great institution like Georgetown University.  I also tried contacting the Manager by email, he didn’t even receive a reply to my email.
I waited over two hours to receive my food. Very disappointed.
We had to wait an hour for our food even though the place was basically empty. Staff was rude when we asked them to check on our food, food wasn't hot when it came out. Won't be back!

I've tried over time to continue to give them chances to make things right. Today was my absolute worst experience ever.  After waiting for over 45 minutes, they've still managed to get my order completely wrong, the order taker behind the take out window looked lost, and there was no sense of urgency from the staff. It was a complete waste of time and effort. In voicing my concerns to the new manager, D.B., he was very apologetic about my concerns. Initially I was done with giving them my business. However,  because I truly do want to see them succeed I may give them another chance in the future, provided I see some major improvements in their service and food quality.

* They're making a serious effort. Tonight was much better. I've adjusted the ranking. Keep it up. Original rating:* Worst service ever. 30 minutes at the bar and still not acknowledged to take an order. Just go to Tombs. Id give 0 stars if I could.

after the management changed this summer (2017), Bulldog has gone downhill so much it's unrecognizable. The staff is condescending, slow, inefficient and at times almost rude. We waited over 45 min for two entrees in an almost empty restaurant (only 3 other tables), they got the order wrong several times, didn't have the only vegan option or some of the drinks, and to top it off the food wasn't even good. So disappointed, will not be going back despite its convenience for on-campus students.

Bulldog Tavern is a s#$t hole.  Do not waste your time or money here.  If I could do 0 stars I would.  I went there 3 times.  First off, all three times service was abysmal.  They take 20-30 min to even get to your order.  The food is not worth waiting for.  The worst part, on top of that is they "act" like a high class, 5 star establishment.  They have idiot students working there who can't take an order or act professionally.  You cannot bring food inside from anywhere else on the campus itself.  This pertains specifically to a food allergy circumstance where they cannot accommodate for a life threatening food allergy.  The manager claimed BS about "you would not be able to do this at any other establishment" as if they are some high class restaurant.  Instead, as paying customers (we ordered multiple drinks and food) they could have accommodated the fact our sole guest member could not eat here.  The manager took no consideration in the fact I was a Georgetown employee and just kept reciting ridiculous rhetoric that "you can't do this, no one else would let you do this".  I have been to hole in the wall places that would either let you bring in outside food, or would be able to accommodate you.  Typical pretentious BS from a place that couldn't accommodate a 10 year olds food needs.  Do not waste your time.

Terrible, terrible service. Consistently, every single time I give it one more try, something is wrong with the order. The staff is also not helpful at all and they don't acknowledge their messup each time an order is missing or wrong. Very inefficient. Definitely giving up on it at this point.
Place is a campus joke. Consistently terrible service. Today I went and my drink that I ordered and asked after 3 times arrived after I'd already finished my main course.
Food is decent and service is getting better! Half-price burgers on Mondays!
Slow service

I'll admit, I'm typically a captive audience. The on campus options are slim. If you aren't in a rush, the food is good and the drinks are affordable. If you are in a rush, there are better options elsewhere.
Can't beat the location on Georgetown's campus looking out to the Potomac, but service could be a little faster

Not amazing, but actually pretty good, esp for a little college bar. Waiters are fantastic and trivia on Thursdays is quite good. Beer selection, not bad, food okay. Overall, if you're on campus, it's worth a stop for a beer.
Everything sucks about this place. Since they serve college students they get to serve crap as food. Anyways, my food was burnt and smelled disgusting, who knows what was in there.
Food was cold and service was super slow. Hope it gets better before another year of school.
Great food at decent price.

Mediocre food for expensive prices. They often don't have things that have been advertised on their menu. The food takes inexplicably long to arrive, even if your party has ordered before the group at another table that's getting their food before you. If you're not a Georgetown student, the location is also going to be hard to find too since it's inside a student center building without a front door of its own to the outside.

Although it's refreshingly cheap for a sit down meal in this part of town, it manages a mix of noise level, mediocre food and truly abysmal service (I say that as someone who couldn't care less about service; I'd just like the items I ordered delivered to my table eventually and itemized correctly on my bill) that make it impossible to recommend.

Bulldog Tavern is a great spot, super convenient to both Georgetown Campus and Georgetown Proper. It's all brand new, and a great atmosphere - the outdoor seating has great views on Rosslyn as well. I recommend the hamburgers, extremely delicious! Hoya Saxa!
This is a lovely new spot on campus with a great beer selection. If you have a chance check it out and sit on the outdoor patio (if it's not DC humid, of course). #hoyasaxa
